modules.description: Provides functions to retrieve lists of package configurations, each containing a name, version, and list of directives. Works with tuples of strings and lists of custom directive values. Used to access predefined sets of packages for different OCaml versions and configuration scenarios.

Handles file system operations such as creating, reading, and modifying project-specific configuration files and user-level binary directories. Works with path strings, JSON data structures, and environment variables to manage installation states. Used to set up isolated OCaml environments and configure user-specific tooling during project initialization.

Provides functions to access and manipulate package configurations, each defined by a name, version, and list of directives. It supports operations on tuples of strings and custom directive lists, enabling retrieval of predefined package sets for various OCaml versions. Users can filter, iterate, or process configurations based on version or directive criteria. For example, it can extract all packages compatible with OCaml 4.14 or collect directives for a specific build scenario.
